editorialSummary.text: Relaxed cafe-style venue specialising in steamed Chinese dumplings presented in bamboo baskets.

text.text:
Authentic little family style dumpling shop in the city that has $1 dumplings on Tuesday and Thursday.

Harbin pork dumplings are a little bland, chicken donggu are very nice and the pork cloud (not incl. in $1 deal) buns are extremely fluffy, but flavour is nothing amazing. Sauces and condiments including chilli oil are provided, and the service is quite quick.

Would come back for the $1 chicken donggu dumplings!

editorialSummary.text: Laid-back restaurant featuring made-to-order fresh pasta dishes, along with pizza & salad.

text.text:
Came here in the sweet spot around 3 at the end of their lunch deals going into their happy hour so enjoyed the best value.

Service was very good with all the staff being friendly and attentive.

Food was satisfying but the difference in dough between the garlic bread and pizza was a shame (or cooking style? I don’t know). Either way the garlic bread was perfect and soft but the pizza was crispy and dry.
If the pizza base was as soft as the garlic bread this would be easy 5 star.

The cocktail was nice but a bit heavy on the soda I think as it was a bit watered down and the flavour went fast

Good value nevertheless, would probably pop in for garlic bread and a drink.

text.text: Too salty. Went to Vapiano Saturday night, which was busy and staff friendly. We sat upstairs at table 61. Cocktails and home made lemonade were nice. We all ordered pasta, two with fettuccine and one with the zoodles. Beef ragu, Gamberi E Spinaci and the Pollo Rosso. Unfortunately, all three dishes were too salty and so we couldn’t eat them. It was really disappointing and I did mention it to staff. The staff member was going to tell the kitchen. I did see another review about salty food, so I hope Vapiano can fix the issue.

editorialSummary.text: Wood-fired pizza and Italian mains in a chic, warehouse-style space with exposed-brick archways.

text.text:
A very stylish and chic Italian restaurant.
Based on the number of reviews on the calamari, I had to try it of course. It did not disappoint! The calamari was beautifully soft and just lightly battered and fried, which gave it a really nice mouth feel. Perfectly seasoned too.
Had the seared scallops which were perfectly cooked. The cauliflower puree was silky smooth... pairing with the crispy pancetta made it super delicious.
The food came really quickly which was fantastic. Only had time for a light lunch today, will definitely come back to try the pizzas and pastas

the service was impeccable, filling our water up whenever it was getting low, taking our order with great timing even with how busy it was. Joel our waiter did such a great job props to him.

The coffee ☕️ was delicious and creamy.

Even though there was a lineup we were served within 10 minutes and meals were put within 15minutes

My girlfriend is vegetarian/vegan and they were able to cater to her needs so 10/10

text.text:
Came here for late lunch early dinner. It was really Impressive how well the staff knew the menu. We shared  pizza, it was the one with pork fennel sausage And rocket.  I give it a 10/10
The  we also shared the duck breast. We told the waiter we where sharing so they plated it on two plates amazing portion, the onion and the radicchio really balanced this dish out so well. The potato was so creamy delicate velvety Texture. I can not fault it. 10/10
For dessert we shared the pear and hazelnut nut cake. I could not taste the pear the Hazelnut was the star of it. It came which a chocolate sauce and some kind of thick cream.. it was like having a Ferrero rocher.

With the welcoming shervice and the style of Restaurant would be perfect for, date night, anniversary. Its very classy and modern. I personally can not wait to go back.

editorialSummary.text: A tranquil space offering classic sushi, sashimi and BBQ dishes amid traditional Japanese decor.

text.text:
A relaxed venue with decent food.
I paid $80 to sit on plastic chairs, with a menu presented in an office works ring binder, so I can't give 5 stars, but I enjoyed both the food and sake so its a solid 4.
Service was quick. You might need a plan for what to do after you finish, where to go next.
You can watch the food being prepared for mild entertainment.

text.text: Had a reservation for 6:30pm on a Saturday night, and were told on entry food might be up to 1hr. This was all sweet with our group as we had 2 hours before our next activity. Food surprisingly took 15 minutes from ordering on the app, and was delicious and fresh and hot! Was a nice little surprise. Our seat upstairs was beautifully appointed, and I love the basil and rosemary plants on each table. Your staff were excellent, courteous, and amazing photographers! There is a bathroom upstairs next to the kitchen/bar for anyone who needs to go, so no having to traipse back downstairs. Wonderful atmosphere on a Saturday night!

text.text:
A great Italian restaurant to grab a quick, easy and tasty lunch. Our food came in 10min after ordering it through the super easy website. Great portion size for the price and I have paid double for a far less tasty pasta dish. I ordered the carbonara with extra mushrooms. I would highly recommend. We ordered the truffle oil pizza and it was on point. I was also impressed with the service. The wait staff were attentive and really fast. The manager even came and checked on us which you don’t get much these days from restaurant managers.

Overall this was an awesome experience and I will be returning to Vapianos very soon.

text.text: We came here (7 people) for a quick lunch. We ordered pizzas and salads. Pizzas were delicious, and then the leafy salad came out. I can only describe it as a very poor and cheap excuse for a 'mixed green leaf' salad. It looked like iceberg lettuce with a sprinkle of balsamic vinegar. For the price, this was very disappointing. I would suggest that the kitchen make a bit of effort here as it lets down an otherwise good menu.
